<p>Both within the context of queer Catholicism and in queerdom in general, I’ve experienced a growing pull away from the things I normally appreciate: sincerity, a sense of community, and daylight. For many young queer people, the queer community can, as a false monolith, present itself as an event that happens one week or month a year during the day, and every weekend at night.</p>
